race.comment: DIFFERENT GRAVY (1) is clearly the horse to beat. He was dominant winning at Listed level at Flemington during Cup week, settling a long way back but charging away to win by two lengths. He'll relish rising to 2000m here with Zahra sticking and this won't take any more winning than last time. If there's a danger, it's CALL DA VINCI (3) who comes through the G2 Sandown Guineas won by Sheza Alibi, who put a space on her rivals. They went slowly in that race and CALL DA VINCI was unsuited back in the field. His late sectionals were the third-fastest in the race and he should appreciate rising to 2000m now. KALEO (2) beat CALL DA VINCI home there albeit with a better run in transit. He's bred to stay and is an each way hope. BRAVE DANZA (4) tried hard behind DIFFERENT GRAVY last time and can stick on for another minor placing. GOLD TOPAZ (8) brings similar form and maps well.
